original: Barthelson, Gustaf (Gösta), rytt-mästare, jägmästare, Skövde, f. 29/7/ 96 i Halna, Skarab. 1., av överjägm. Gustaf B. o. Anna Walhn. G. 27 m. Lily Petzén. Barn: Birgitta f. 30, Clemens 38. — Stud:ex. 15, utex. fr. skogshögsk. 22. Stud. i Kanada o. USA 23. Fänrik i SmåJ. husarreg. res. 17, und:löjtn. 19, löjtn. 24, ryttm. 36. Bitr. länsjägm. i Skarab. 1. 24-25. Privat verksamhet 25-39. Förordn. som exped :o’ff. v. HL milo i Skövde sed. 42.
translated: Barthelson, Gustaf (Gösta), captain of cavalry, forestry inspector, Skövde, b. 29/7/96 in Halna, Skaraborgs län, son of senior forestry inspector Gustaf B. and Anna Walhn. Married to Lily Petzén in 1927, with two children: Birgitta, born in 1930 and Clemens, born in 1938. Gustaf passed his matriculation exam in 1915 and graduated from the Forestry School in 1922. He studied in Canada and USA in 1923. He served in the Småland Hussar Regiment as ensign in 1917, as sub-lieutenant in 1919, as lieutenant in 1924, and as captain of cavalry in 1936. He was deputy county forestry inspector in Skaraborgs län between 1924 and 1925 and worked in private enterprise between 1925 and 1939. He was appointed as an expedition officer for the Home Guard in Skövde in 1942.
